---
import Base from '../layouts/base.astro'

import '../styles/global.css'
---

<Base title="bryanvelo.so" description="The work of Bryan Veloso.">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h1>I am not your typical web designer.</h1>
    <p>I am a creative driven by my hobbies. I am unapologetic when I fight for end users. I thrive on supporting the unsupported. I believe AI exists to support and not supplant.</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <a href="/portfolio" class="group">
        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm transition duration-200 hover:shadow-md"
        >
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 group-hover:text-amber-700">
            Portfolio
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            View my professional work across companies like GitHub, Twitch, and
            Facebook, as well as personal projects.
          </p>
          <div class="text-amber-700 flex items-center">
            <span>View portfolio</span>
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              class="h-4 w-4 ml-1 transition-transform duration-200 group-hover:translate-x-1"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">About Me</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          I specialize in user interface design, with a focus on creating
          experiences that are both visually appealing and highly functional.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          When I'm not designing, I enjoy streaming, gaming, and sharing my
          knowledge with the community.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
“The guy that said "HOLY!" during the [Final Fantasy XIV] Shadowbringers E3 trailer.”
—Fusionx, @rofldrg
“Who remembers the OG’s of the web? 456 Berea Street, Stop Design, Mezzoblue, Avalonstar, SimpleBits, Authentic Boredom… Miss those days.”
—Noah Stokes, @motherfuton
“Wait until you see what he can do with a semicolon.”
—Michael McHugh, @mmchugh
“What's the equivalent of punk rock but for the tech industry? Because I feel like you are it.”
—Elsie Ng, @_elsieng
“He did that bowling thing, but that was it. 😜”
—Dustin Diaz, @ded        
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>
